Money Bin Additions — Practical Idea Seeds

1. Reasoning Move Cards

Create a deck of reasoning operators (like flash cards or a digital library).

Example cards:
	•	Split — break system into components
	•	Rotate — view from another domain
	•	Invert — reverse cause/effect
	•	Compress — summarize invariant
	•	Expand — generate variants
	•	Anchor — attach to real measurement

You could build a prompt generator that randomly draws 3–4 cards and forces creative reasoning.

Impact: ⭐⭐⭐⭐
Feasibility: ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

⸻

